<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-04"><hi rend="italic">October 4,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Gresham requests further particulars and asks what the Turkish Government
                        claims, what ground the arrest was based on, and whether the men were
                        arrested because they violated some law or order of the Turkish Government
                        by returning.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>